# SPA fallback — any path that doesn't match a static file falls back to
# the prerendered index.html so React Router can handle client-side routing.
#
# This is honoured by Cloudflare Pages AND by Workers Static Assets (the
# not_found_handling: single-page-application setting in wrangler.jsonc
# is the primary mechanism; this file is a safety net for the Pages path
# and for direct-deploy scenarios).
#
# The 200 status code (not 301/302) means the URL in the browser stays the
# same — the user sees /projects/pyrope, but the server serves index.html
# and React Router takes over.
/*    /index.html   200
